The paper deals with wireless networks and their capacity analysis, which falls under the information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the large-deviations behavior of certain sums of dependent random variables, which is related to statistical mechanics (cs.SI) and systems and control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper uses tools from large random matrix theory, which is a sub-field of multimedia (cs.MM).
